pr_body:
Closes #11.

I have tested this manually as well with a local install and it does what I was looking for.

@kopf What do you think?

I've added support for Flickr via OAuth 1.0 Core which allows you to associate and later publish photos. I've also added a new context processor that makes it easy to know which accounts are available in templates so that you can adjust the UI accordingly, e.g.

    {% if social_auth.flickr %}
        {# show Flickr publishing form #}
    {% endif %}
    {% if social_auth.google_oauth2 %}
        {# show Picasa publishing form #}
    {% endif %}

Also updated the README.

Made a few other tweaks to make them more consistent in style.

@tvansteenburgh @abentley @johnsca: I wanted to make sure that when people encounter this library the first time, they encounter our loop helper, and aren't turned off by the details of standing up an asyncio event loop.

We are leaking a lot of connections right now which is causing me to hit connection limits. 

This change addresses the bugs that we fixed in #328 by using a frozenset to pass the dict to `create_engine`. We also fix the issue with `drop` by explicitly removing the table from the metadata.

@cpcloud
